<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="843" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/290.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Dr. <persName type="to">Roland P. Falkner</persName>, Financial
                                Representative of the Republic of Liberia</hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence
                            relative to the negotiations for the rehabilitation of the finances of
                            Liberia, you are informed that a note has been received from the French
                            Ambassador, at this capital in which he advised the Department that his
                            Government has appointed Mr. Frédéric Wolf, Deputy Colonial
                            Administrator of the Second Class, as the French Receiver of Liberian
                            Customs, in accordance with the provisions of the Liberian Loan
                            Agreement.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>